digi-inking? nah i tred it once and it takes way to long, i find it easyer to ink by hand, heres what i do<br>
<br>
step 1:  get your drawing and ink it by hand, i find that a 0.2 artliner pens work best.<br>
<br>
step 2: scan your image in at 300 dpi in black and white and don't worry bout ajusting anything<br>
<br>
step 3: once scaned in select the hold of the image and copy it, make a new layer and past it onto the new layer called &quot;outline&quot;<br>
<br>
step 4: go to the background layer and delete the hole layer, make a new layer, go to the layer options tab at the top of the screen and select &quot;make layer background&quot;, this is best done when the background color it white <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
step 5: select the &quot;outlines&quot; layer and go to the chanle tab in your color and layer tray, then clikc on the little circuler thingy ... this sould make lots of lines flash on the image were the balck is, press delete (you may need to inverse the image first if the black dissapers).<br>
<br>
step 6: if you go to the background layer and press the hide button you should see that the lines are still there but the white isn't <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , do what you want to the image and zoom out to about 25% then chage the image size to match it at 100% ((e.g if its a a4 page that you scanned in at 300dpi then change the image size to 600 or 500)) wolla!, it should look clean and neat when veiw as a page, but when you zoom in it looks like a bunch a pixels <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=redddragon501>ReddDragon501</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/15/03 6:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=376.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/redd-dragon/EZSIG.jpg  height=67 width=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ahhh... ha?</span><hr size=1> Yeah Hidro ... I try to do that too... the whole post your character sketch when the character is introduced thing... i think it just gives a whole better feel and lets those that dont know.... Know something about your character and his/her motives int he fight.....<br>
